<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880829-0026 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Emery Air Freight Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EAF </CO><TEXT>   Emery Air Freight Corp., Wilton, Conn., said its bank lenders have agreed to extend the maturity of its outstanding bank debt until Oct. 15 from Wednesday to complete a financial restructuring of the air freight concern.    The financial restructuring involves refunding Emery's airport revenue bonds and arranging a revolving credit facility. Emery wouldn't elaborate on the restructuring and said the terms aren't yet completed.    The company said it has been working with James D. Wolfensohn Inc., its financial adviser, and Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. on a financial restructuring that will satisfy its present debt obligations and provide ongoing liquidity. A spokeswoman said that as of June 30, Emery had $47.6 million of short-term debt outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>